solution.p:
Derivando em relação a x obtemos
0 = 6 x^2 y^2 + 4 x^3 y\frac{dy}{dx}
-6 xy-3 x^2\frac{dy}{dx}, ou 6 xy - 6 x^2y^2= \left(4 x^3 y
- 3 x^2\right)\frac{dy}{dx}
. Portanto, \frac{dx}{dy} = \frac{6 x y -
 6 x^2 y^2}{4 x^3y-3 x^2}.

p.me:
\begin{array}{rcl} f'(x) \amp =\amp  \displaystyle\frac{8}{1+ (3 \sin(4 x))^2} \frac{d}{dx} (3 \sin(4 x))
\\ \amp =\amp  \displaystyle\frac{8}{1+ 9 \sin^2(4 x)} (3\cdot 4  \cos (4 x))
\\ \amp =\amp  \displaystyle \frac{96 \cos (4 x)}{1+ 9 \sin^2(4 x)} 
\end{array}

\begin{array}{rcl}
   \dfrac{d}{dx}[7 \sin x  + 3 \cos y] \amp =\amp  \dfrac{d}{dx}[2]\\
   \amp \amp \\
   7 \cos x - 3 \sin y \dfrac{dy}{dx} \amp =\amp  0 \\
   \amp \amp \\
   \dfrac{dy}{dx} \amp =\amp  \dfrac{7 \cos x}{3 \sin y}
  \end{array}

\begin{array}{rcl}
    \dfrac{d^2y}{dx^2} \amp =\amp  
    \dfrac{d}{dx}\left[  \dfrac{7 \cos x}{3 \sin y} \right] \\
    \amp \amp \\
    \amp =\amp  \dfrac{  3 \sin y(-7 \sin x) - (7 \cos x)(3 \cos y \cdot y')}
    {9 \sin^2 y} \\
    \amp \amp \\
    \amp =\amp  \dfrac{-21( \sin x \sin y + \cos x \cos y \cdot y')}
    {9 \sin^2 y} \\
    \amp =\amp  \dfrac{-7( \sin x \sin y + \cos x \cos y \cdot y')}
    {3 \sin^2 y} \\
  \end{array}

solution.p:
Para a resposta final, substitua
y' = \dfrac{7 \cos x}{3 \sin y}.
\begin{array}{rcl}
   \frac{d^2y}{dx^2} \amp =\amp  \dfrac{-7\left( \sin x \sin y +
   \cos x \cos y \cdot \dfrac{7 \cos x}{3 \sin y}\right)}
    {3 \sin^2 y}\\
    \amp \amp \\
    \amp =\amp  \dfrac{-7\left( \sin x \sin y + 
    \frac{7}{3} \cos^2 x \cot y\right)}
    {3 \sin^2 y}\\
  \end{array}
